	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001922_0001"><!--pb/@n='30r'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="right"><date when="1863-05-30">Saturday 30 May 
<lb/>1863</date></p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName><choice><abbr>HW</abbr><expan>Horace Waller</expan></choice></persName></p>
<lb/><p>We send 
<lb/>back the books with  
<lb/>many thanks for 
<lb/>the use of them. 
<lb/>they are somewhat 
<lb/>damaged by cockroaches 
<lb/>and one is not 
<lb/>at hand, possibly 
<lb/>it may hence gone 
<lb/>down - I mean 
<lb/>the volume of "All 
<lb/>the year round<supplied>"</supplied>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001922_0002"><!--pb/@n='30v'--></pb>
<lb/>I retain <persName>Keble</persName> for 
<lb/>a little longer.</p>
<lb/><p>I am sorry that 
<lb/>you did not 
<lb/>succeed according 
<lb/>to all our wishes 
<lb/>and your own 
<lb/>I guess you uttered 
<lb/>some of your 
<lb/>terrific puns on 
<lb/>the way &amp; made 
<lb/><persName>Procter</persName> ill. I 
<lb/>escaped relapse 
<lb/>myself by holding 

    

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001922_0003"><!--pb/@n='31r'--></pb>
<lb/>in my breath as 
<lb/>I read them. send 
<lb/>a few more I wish 
<lb/>to try if they will 
<lb/>exorcise the cockroaches 
<lb/>Better luck next 
<lb/>time for you all 
<lb/>I hope <persName>Meller</persName> will 
<lb/>cure <persName>Procter</persName> as 
<lb/>quickly as he did 
<lb/>his own case. 
<lb/>Yesterday for 
<lb/>the first time 
<lb/>I walked a little 

    

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001922_0004"><!--pb/@n='31v'--></pb>
<lb/>without feeling as 
<lb/>if I should faint 
<lb/>this may be the 
<lb/>effects of the iron 
<lb/>which I have taken 
<lb/>three times.</p>
<lb/><p>With good wishes 
<lb/>for you all I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName><choice><abbr>DL</abbr><expan>David Livingstone</expan></choice></persName> His Mark <!-- here DL draws a little Cross AJS 12/1 --></p>
			
</div>
